@startuml NVIC_Class_Diagram
title NVIC Driver — Static Interrupt Controller Interface

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F5FAFF
    BorderColor #2C7FB8
    ArrowColor #2C7FB8
}

class NVIC <<static>> {
    +{static} enableIRQ(IRQn_Type irq) : void
    +{static} disableIRQ(IRQn_Type irq) : void
    +{static} setPriority(IRQn_Type irq, uint8_t priority) : void
}

note right of NVIC
  All methods are static — NVIC
  is a hardware singleton, not
  an owned instance.

  enableIRQ() sets the matching
  bit in NVIC_ISER[n].
  disableIRQ() sets NVIC_ICER[n].
  setPriority() writes NVIC_IPR[n];
  hardware only implements the
  top 4 bits of the priority field
  (STM32F4 uses 4 priority bits).
end note

class "Peripheral Driver\n(EXTI, USART, ...)" as Peripheral

Peripheral ..> NVIC : NVIC::enableIRQ(...)\nNVIC::setPriority(...)

@enduml
